---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro'
---

<Layout
  title="About"
  description="How Kube Schemas is built — schema generation pipeline, repository structure, and static API"
>
  <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-12">

    <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold text-zinc-900 mb-2">How it's built</h1>
    <p class="text-lg text-zinc-500 mb-12">
      A fully static site generated from open-source controller repositories. No server required — schemas are extracted at build time and committed to the repository.
    </p>

    <!-- Overview -->
    <section class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-zinc-800 mb-4">Overview</h2>
      <div class="bg-white border border-zinc-200 rounded-xl p-6 shadow-sm space-y-3 text-sm text-zinc-600 leading-relaxed">
        <p>
          Each controller's schemas are generated by cloning the controller's source repository, running
          <code class="font-mono bg-zinc-100 px-1 rounded">openapi-gen</code> over its Go types, and converting
          the resulting OpenAPI spec to individual JSON Schema files via
          <code class="font-mono bg-zinc-100 px-1 rounded">openapi2jsonschema</code>.
          For Kubernetes built-in types, the upstream <code class="font-mono bg-zinc-100 px-1 rounded">swagger.json</code> is used directly.
        </p>
        <p>
          CRD-based controllers additionally spin up a live <code class="font-mono bg-zinc-100 px-1 rounded">kube-apiserver</code> via
          <code class="font-mono bg-zinc-100 px-1 rounded">envtest</code> to capture authoritative resource discovery
          (kind, group, version, scope, short names) and a second set of schemas from the live OpenAPI endpoint.
        </p>
        <p>
          The generated schemas, CRD YAMLs, and resource index files are committed to the repository under
          <code class="font-mono bg-zinc-100 px-1 rounded">schemas/ORG/REPO/VERSION/</code>.
          This site is an <a href="https://astro.build" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-violet-600 hover:text-violet-800">Astro</a> static
          site that reads those files at build time — no runtime server or database.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Repository layout -->
    <section class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-zinc-800 mb-4">Repository layout</h2>
      <div class="bg-zinc-900 rounded-xl overflow-hidden shadow-sm">
        <pre class="p-5 text-sm text-zinc-300 leading-relaxed overflow-x-auto"><code>{`schemas/
  ORG/REPO/
    index.yaml              # controller metadata (name, GitHub URL)
    VERSION/
      index.yaml            # resource list with GVK, scope, short names
      crds.yaml             # all CRDs as a single multi-document YAML
      crd/                  # individual CRD YAML files
      discovery/            # raw API discovery JSON files (k8s ≥ 1.28)
      json-schema/
        source/             # schemas from controller source (openapi-gen)
          _definitions.json
          KIND-GROUP-VERSION.json
        live/               # schemas from live kube-apiserver (envtest)
          _definitions.json
          KIND-GROUP-VERSION.json
      openapi/
        source.json         # merged OpenAPI spec (intermediate)
        live.json           # filtered spec from live kube-apiserver

config/
  ORG/REPO/VERSION/
    config.yaml             # generation parameters
    patch.diff              # optional: patches applied to controller source
    patch-vendor.diff       # optional: patches applied after go mod vendor

tools/
  generate.py               # single-controller generation pipeline
  run.py                    # parallel runner (N Docker containers)
  discover.py               # populates index.yaml from API discovery
  envtest.py                # live CRD discovery via kube-apiserver
  envtest_openapi.py        # captures /openapi/v2 from envtest

site/                       # this Astro site`}</code></pre>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Generation pipeline -->
    <section class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-zinc-800 mb-4">Generation pipeline</h2>
      <div class="space-y-3">
        {[
          { n: '1', label: 'Clone', desc: 'git clone --depth 1 --branch VERSION the controller repository' },
          { n: '2', label: 'Patch source', desc: 'Apply patch.diff — typically adds +k8s:openapi-gen=true markers to doc.go files' },
          { n: '3', label: 'Vendor', desc: 'go mod vendor downloads all dependencies' },
          { n: '4', label: 'Patch vendor', desc: 'Apply patch-vendor.diff — adds openapi markers to vendored dependency packages if needed' },
          { n: '5', label: 'openapi-gen', desc: 'Generates openapi_generated.go from annotated Go types in the specified packages' },
          { n: '6', label: 'Build OpenAPI spec', desc: 'A small generated Go program merges all OpenAPI definitions into a single openapi.json' },
          { n: '7', label: 'openapi2jsonschema', desc: 'Converts the OpenAPI spec into per-resource JSON Schema files under json-schema/source/' },
          { n: '8', label: 'Collect CRDs', desc: 'Copies individual CRD YAMLs, writes crds.yaml, populates index.yaml resource list' },
          { n: '9', label: 'envtest (optional)', desc: 'Starts a live kube-apiserver, installs CRDs, overwrites index.yaml with authoritative discovery data' },
          { n: '10', label: 'Live schemas (optional)', desc: 'Fetches /openapi/v2 from the same API server, produces json-schema/live/ and openapi/live.json' },
        ].map(({ n, label, desc }) => (
          <div class="flex gap-4 bg-white border border-zinc-200 rounded-xl px-5 py-4 shadow-sm">
            <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-7 h-7 rounded-full bg-violet-100 text-violet-700 text-xs font-bold flex items-center justify-center mt-0.5">
              {n}
            </div>
            <div>
              <span class="text-sm font-semibold text-zinc-800">{label}</span>
              <span class="text-sm text-zinc-500 ml-2">— {desc}</span>
            </div>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>
      <p class="mt-4 text-sm text-zinc-500">
        Kubernetes built-in schemas skip steps 1–4 and use the upstream <code class="font-mono bg-zinc-100 px-1 rounded">swagger.json</code> directly.
        Steps 9–10 require <code class="font-mono bg-zinc-100 px-1 rounded">$ENVTEST_BIN_DIR/kube-apiserver</code> and are run inside the Docker builder image.
      </p>
    </section>

    <!-- Resource classification -->
    <section class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-zinc-800 mb-4">Resource classification</h2>
      <div class="bg-white border border-zinc-200 rounded-xl divide-y divide-zinc-100 shadow-sm text-sm">
        <div class="px-5 py-4">
          <span class="font-semibold text-zinc-800">User-managed</span>
          <span class="text-zinc-500 ml-2">— resources intended to be created and managed directly by users (e.g. <code class="font-mono bg-zinc-100 px-1 rounded">Deployment</code>, <code class="font-mono bg-zinc-100 px-1 rounded">Service</code>). Shown normally.</span>
        </div>
        <div class="px-5 py-4">
          <span class="inline-flex items-center px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded text-xs font-medium bg-zinc-100 text-zinc-500 border border-zinc-200 mr-2">system</span>
          <span class="font-semibold text-zinc-800">Auto-detected</span>
          <span class="text-zinc-500 ml-2">— resources whose API verbs do not include <code class="font-mono bg-zinc-100 px-1 rounded">delete</code>, or that belong to <code class="font-mono bg-zinc-100 px-1 rounded">internal.apiserver.k8s.io</code>. These are infrastructure-only (e.g. <code class="font-mono bg-zinc-100 px-1 rounded">TokenReview</code>, <code class="font-mono bg-zinc-100 px-1 rounded">Binding</code>).</span>
        </div>
        <div class="px-5 py-4">
          <span class="inline-flex items-center px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded text-xs font-medium bg-zinc-100 text-zinc-500 border border-zinc-200 mr-2">system</span>
          <span class="font-semibold text-zinc-800">Manually listed</span>
          <span class="text-zinc-500 ml-2">— resources that are user-accessible but system-managed (e.g. <code class="font-mono bg-zinc-100 px-1 rounded">Endpoints</code>, <code class="font-mono bg-zinc-100 px-1 rounded">EndpointSlice</code>), listed in the controller's <code class="font-mono bg-zinc-100 px-1 rounded">index.yaml</code> under <code class="font-mono bg-zinc-100 px-1 rounded">systemResources</code>.</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Schema sources -->
    <section class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-zinc-800 mb-4">Schema sources</h2>
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4 text-sm">
        <div class="bg-white border border-zinc-200 rounded-xl p-5 shadow-sm">
          <div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-2">
            <span class="text-xs px-2 py-0.5 rounded font-mono bg-violet-100 text-violet-700">source</span>
            <span class="font-semibold text-zinc-800">Controller source</span>
          </div>
          <p class="text-zinc-500 leading-relaxed">
            Schema derived from Go type annotations in the controller source code via <code class="font-mono bg-zinc-100 px-1 rounded">openapi-gen</code>.
            Available for all controllers that use the shared generation pipeline.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-white border border-zinc-200 rounded-xl p-5 shadow-sm">
          <div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-2">
            <span class="text-xs px-2 py-0.5 rounded font-mono bg-emerald-100 text-emerald-700">live</span>
            <span class="font-semibold text-zinc-800">Live kube-apiserver</span>
          </div>
          <p class="text-zinc-500 leading-relaxed">
            Schema captured from a live <code class="font-mono bg-zinc-100 px-1 rounded">kube-apiserver</code> running via
            <code class="font-mono bg-zinc-100 px-1 rounded">envtest</code> with CRDs installed.
            Reflects exactly what the API server accepts and validates.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Static API -->
    <section class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-zinc-800 mb-4">Static JSON API</h2>
      <p class="text-sm text-zinc-600 mb-4 leading-relaxed">
        The site exposes a machine-readable API as static JSON files, generated alongside the HTML at build time.
      </p>
      <div class="bg-white border border-zinc-200 rounded-xl divide-y divide-zinc-100 shadow-sm font-mono text-sm">
        <div class="flex items-start gap-4 px-5 py-4">
          <code class="text-violet-700 whitespace-nowrap">/api/v1/index.json</code>
          <span class="text-zinc-500">List of all controllers with version arrays and URLs</span>
        </div>
        <div class="flex items-start gap-4 px-5 py-4">
          <code class="text-violet-700 whitespace-nowrap">/api/v1/&#123;org&#125;/&#123;repo&#125;/index.json</code>
          <span class="text-zinc-500">Controller metadata and version list</span>
        </div>
        <div class="flex items-start gap-4 px-5 py-4">
          <code class="text-violet-700 whitespace-nowrap">/api/v1/&#123;org&#125;/&#123;repo&#125;/&#123;version&#125;/index.json</code>
          <span class="text-zinc-500">Full resource list for a version with schema file URLs</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Tooling -->
    <section class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-zinc-800 mb-4">Tooling</h2>
      <div class="bg-white border border-zinc-200 rounded-xl divide-y divide-zinc-100 shadow-sm text-sm">
        {[
          { tool: 'openapi-gen', desc: 'Generates Go OpenAPI definitions from annotated types', src: 'k8s.io/kube-openapi/cmd/openapi-gen' },
          { tool: 'openapi2jsonschema', desc: 'Converts OpenAPI specs to JSON Schema files', src: 'instrumenta/openapi2jsonschema' },
          { tool: 'setup-envtest', desc: 'Downloads envtest binaries (etcd + kube-apiserver + kubectl)', src: 'sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime/tools/setup-envtest' },
          { tool: 'Astro', desc: 'Static site generator powering this UI', src: 'astro.build' },
          { tool: 'Docker', desc: 'Builds an isolated schema-builder image with all tools pre-installed', src: '' },
        ].map(({ tool, desc, src }) => (
          <div class="flex items-start gap-4 px-5 py-4">
            <code class="flex-shrink-0 w-44 font-mono text-violet-700">{tool}</code>
            <div>
              <span class="text-zinc-700">{desc}</span>
              {src && <span class="ml-2 text-zinc-400 font-mono text-xs">{src}</span>}
            </div>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Claude Code -->
    <section class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-zinc-800 mb-4">Adding controllers with Claude Code</h2>
      <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-amber-50 to-orange-50 border border-amber-200 rounded-xl p-6 shadow-sm">
        <div class="flex items-start gap-4 mb-5">
          <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-10 h-10 rounded-xl bg-amber-100 border border-amber-200 flex items-center justify-center text-lg">
            ✦
          </div>
          <div>
            <p class="font-semibold text-zinc-800 mb-1">Claude Code is the recommended way to add new controllers and versions</p>
            <p class="text-sm text-zinc-600 leading-relaxed">
              The generation pipeline has enough moving parts — Go module paths, openapi-gen flags, host conversion rules,
              patch files — that getting everything right on the first try is non-trivial.
              Claude Code reads <code class="font-mono bg-white/70 px-1 rounded">CLAUDE.md</code> automatically and has full context
              of every convention in this repository, making it exceptionally good at this task.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="space-y-4 text-sm">
          <div class="bg-white/70 rounded-lg px-4 py-3 border border-amber-100">
            <p class="font-semibold text-zinc-700 mb-1">Adding a new controller</p>
            <p class="text-zinc-500 leading-relaxed">
              Describe the controller — its GitHub URL, the version you want, and any known quirks.
              Claude Code will create <code class="font-mono bg-amber-50 px-1 rounded">config/ORG/REPO/VERSION/config.yaml</code>,
              determine the correct <code class="font-mono bg-amber-50 px-1 rounded">openapi_gen_packages</code> and
              <code class="font-mono bg-amber-50 px-1 rounded">host_conversion_rules</code> by inspecting the controller source,
              run generation, and iterate on any errors.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="bg-white/70 rounded-lg px-4 py-3 border border-amber-100">
            <p class="font-semibold text-zinc-700 mb-1">Adding a new version of an existing controller</p>
            <p class="text-zinc-500 leading-relaxed">
              Point Claude Code at the existing <code class="font-mono bg-amber-50 px-1 rounded">config.yaml</code> for that controller
              and name the new version tag. It will copy and update the config, adapt patches if needed,
              run generation, and handle any dependency bumps or API changes introduced in that version.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="bg-white/70 rounded-lg px-4 py-3 border border-amber-100">
            <p class="font-semibold text-zinc-700 mb-1">Debugging generation failures</p>
            <p class="text-zinc-500 leading-relaxed">
              Paste the error log and Claude Code can diagnose it — whether it's a mismatched
              <code class="font-mono bg-amber-50 px-1 rounded">type_aliases</code> format, a missing package in
              <code class="font-mono bg-amber-50 px-1 rounded">openapi_gen_packages</code>, a patch that no longer
              applies cleanly, or a <code class="font-mono bg-amber-50 px-1 rounded">host_conversion_rules</code> prefix collision.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <p class="mt-5 text-xs text-zinc-400 leading-relaxed">
          Claude Code is Anthropic's CLI for Claude — install it with
          <code class="font-mono bg-white/70 px-1 rounded">npm install -g @anthropic-ai/claude-code</code>,
          then run <code class="font-mono bg-white/70 px-1 rounded">claude</code> from the repository root.
          The repository's <code class="font-mono bg-white/70 px-1 rounded">CLAUDE.md</code> is loaded automatically
          as project context.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Source -->
    <div class="bg-violet-50 border border-violet-200 rounded-xl px-6 py-5 flex items-center justify-between">
      <div>
        <p class="font-semibold text-zinc-800 mb-0.5">Open source</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-zinc-500">Generation scripts, schema data, and this site are all in one repository.</p>
      </div>
      <a
        href="https://github.com/iponweb/schemas"
        target="_blank"
        rel="noopener noreferrer"
        class="flex-shrink-0 inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-4 py-2 bg-white border border-zinc-200 rounded-lg text-sm font-medium text-zinc-700 hover:border-violet-300 hover:text-violet-700 transition-colors shadow-sm"
      >
        <svg class="w-4 h-4" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
          <path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M12 2C6.477 2 2 6.484 2 12.017c0 4.425 2.865 8.18 6.839 9.504.5.092.682-.217.682-.483 0-.237-.008-.868-.013-1.703-2.782.605-3.369-1.343-3.369-1.343-.454-1.158-1.11-1.466-1.11-1.466-.908-.62.069-.608.069-.608 1.003.07 1.531 1.032 1.531 1.032.892 1.53 2.341 1.088 2.91.832.092-.647.35-1.088.636-1.338-2.22-.253-4.555-1.113-4.555-4.951 0-1.093.39-1.988 1.029-2.688-.103-.253-.446-1.272.098-2.65 0 0 .84-.27 2.75 1.026A9.564 9.564 0 0112 6.844c.85.004 1.705.115 2.504.337 1.909-1.296 2.747-1.027 2.747-1.027.546 1.379.202 2.398.1 2.651.64.7 1.028 1.595 1.028 2.688 0 3.848-2.339 4.695-4.566 4.943.359.309.678.92.678 1.855 0 1.338-.012 2.419-.012 2.747 0 .268.18.58.688.482A10.019 10.019 0 0022 12.017C22 6.484 17.522 2 12 2z" clip-rule="evenodd" />
        </svg>
        iponweb/schemas
      </a>
    </div>

  </div>
</Layout>
